1
00:00:27,820 --> 00:00:32,320
♪During the dark night♪

2
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,940
♪A guiding light♪

3
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:36,920
♪Just like you♪

4
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:42,290
♪Makes life turn bright♪

5
00:00:42,550 --> 00:00:47,540
♪Breaking free from darkness♪

6
00:00:47,540 --> 00:00:51,130
♪You gave me strength♪

7
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:53,810
♪Running for truth♪

8
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:58,440
♪I find my path♪

9
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:03,090
♪Drawing on the hope♪

10
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:06,740
♪That you render me♪

11
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,870
♪In this long journey♪

12
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:13,940
♪I run on lightly♪

13
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:33,120
=Reborn=

14
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:35,080
(Adapted from the serialized work "Reborn"
by Qiang Yu)

15
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:38,380
Qiao Beiyu didn't die from illness.

16
00:01:38,380 --> 00:01:39,280
She died by suicide.

17
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,460
The illness was detected early.

18
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:43,830
She followed the treatment plan.

19
00:01:44,380 --> 00:01:46,270
She actually could've lived a long life.

20
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:48,160
Someone posted her medical info

21
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,380
and personal details online.

22
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:13,710
Hello?

23
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:15,740
Hello? Beiyu?

24
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:16,990
Who are you looking for?

25
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:18,340
Is this Qiao Beiyu?

26
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:19,390
Hello?

27
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,710
Who do you want to talk to?

28
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:22,300
Is this Beiyu's number or not?

29
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:22,920
Wrong number.

30
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,180
The call actually went through.

31
00:02:24,580 --> 00:02:25,510
Please stop calling.

32
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:26,740
Just stop calling!

33
00:02:26,740 --> 00:02:29,270
Tell Beiyu to pick up.
How did she get sick?

34
00:02:30,110 --> 00:02:31,430
What more do you people want?

35
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:33,020
I'm begging you.

36
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:33,990
Please, I'm begging.

37
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:36,780
Please stop calling, okay?

38
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:38,670
You're heartless.

39
00:02:39,990 --> 00:02:41,020
(After that,)

40
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:44,390
she was bombarded
with messages and calls.

41
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:47,230
Some creeps used
the chance to harass her.

42
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:50,460
(Even more were strangers
pretending to be righteous,)

43
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:52,550
(shaming her
from their moral high ground,)

44
00:02:52,550 --> 00:02:53,510
(tearing her down.)

45
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,460
(She dropped out
of Huanzhou Art School.)

46
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:01,580
(Then, on the night
of Lunar New Year's Eve,)

47
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:04,430
(she quietly left the hospital.)

48
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:33,670
Bei...

49
00:05:15,712 --> 00:05:22,737
=Episode 19=
(Beiyu's Camcorder)

50
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:34,420
She...

51
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:37,710
She was always so timid.
Why would she even do that?

52
00:05:43,390 --> 00:05:45,150
Maybe for Qiao Beiyu,

53
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:49,270
the thought of living
scared her more than dying did.

54
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:57,150
Now I understand why our parents thought

55
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:59,220
keeping quiet and hiding the truth

56
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,870
was the best way to protect us.

57
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:06,070
Because gossip really can kill someone.

58
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:09,950
It killed Qiao Beiyu
right in front of our parents.

59
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:16,830
(I will find the person
who started those rumors.)

60
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:19,950
(They were the last straw
that pushed Beiyu over the edge.)

61
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:24,040
Everyone,

62
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:25,630
before you go, I have something to say.

63
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:27,240
The entrance exam is in two days.

64
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,580
Our school will be a testing site.

65
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:29,830
So before you leave today,

66
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:31,540
make sure the classroom is cleaned up.

67
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:32,100
Is that clear?

68
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:32,900
Yes.

69
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,830
Take everything out of your desks.

70
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:35,510
Bring it home

71
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,580
or throw it away.

72
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:37,540
And also,

73
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:40,980
clean off any cheat sheets
or notes written on your desks.

74
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:42,510
I want them completely gone.

75
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:44,460
Sir, there aren't any cheat sheets.

76
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:45,580
Don't accuse us.

77
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:46,710
Ye Zilin,

78
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,310
your desk is covered

79
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:49,340
in chemistry formulas.

80
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,020
I usually don't say anything

81
00:06:51,020 --> 00:06:52,710
because I want to give you all a break.

82
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:53,510
But now,

83
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,460
you must wipe their desks clean.

84
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,070
Class rep, check the place.

85
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,580
I'll carry out the mission.

86
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:05,630
Qingyu.

87
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:21,310
This is everything
I've summed up for the exam.

88
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:22,980
You're giving it all to me?

89
00:07:23,220 --> 00:07:24,220
Take it.

90
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:25,420
The exam is in two days.

91
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:26,630
I won't need it anymore.

92
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:28,460
Keep it and take your time.

93
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:29,980
Thanks.

94
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:38,020
Qingyu.

95
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:42,460
I've decided
to get treatment for my dad.

96
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,980
I borrowed money from my aunts.

97
00:07:48,340 --> 00:07:49,310
I signed an IOU.

98
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:50,900
It's a total of 200 grand.

99
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:54,750
Are you sure about this?

100
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:55,870
Yeah.

101
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:58,070
I'm doing this

102
00:07:58,220 --> 00:08:00,070
not because of the gossip outside.

103
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:01,870
It's because I realized...

104
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:06,270
I still love my dad.

105
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:11,630
I want to save him.

106
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,580
I don't want to have regrets.

107
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:17,980
You borrowed money to treat your dad.

108
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:19,660
Will your mom be okay with that?

109
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:23,540
Honestly, I don't think my mom

110
00:08:23,630 --> 00:08:25,150
cares that much about the money.

111
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:27,340
She just doesn't want to burden me.

112
00:08:31,630 --> 00:08:35,020
If she were the one who got sick,

113
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:38,020
she would've chosen
to give up treatment too.

114
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:40,150
Qingyu.

115
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:44,870
I've always admired you and Ming Sheng.

116
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:53,180
You both have the courage
to stand up to the world

117
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:55,390
and the guts to face the consequences.

118
00:08:58,900 --> 00:08:59,900
From now on,

119
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:02,660
I want to be someone with courage

120
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:03,820
and responsibility too.

121
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:28,540
Mom?

122
00:09:30,180 --> 00:09:31,870
Mom, what happened to your foot?

123
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:33,200
I'm okay. I sprained it a little.

124
00:09:37,870 --> 00:09:38,660
Qingyu,

125
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:41,940
that time your mom came
to the hospital to see my mom,

126
00:09:42,780 --> 00:09:43,990
she wanted to comfort her,

127
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:46,150
so she talked about the past.

128
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:50,300
She said after your sister passed away,

129
00:09:50,780 --> 00:09:53,180
she almost jumped
out the hospital window.

130
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:54,820
It's just a small sprain, don't worry.

131
00:09:56,110 --> 00:09:58,780
Luckily, two nurses passing
by stopped her.

132
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:00,700
Come on, let's go.

133
00:10:01,230 --> 00:10:02,020
Let's get going.

134
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:03,020
Leave it to me.

135
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:05,940
You can't.

136
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:06,990
Can you even ride this?

137
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:08,350
I'm grown up now.

138
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:11,780
Alright.

139
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,270
There are lots of cars.

140
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:17,660
She also said
if it weren't for you and your brother,

141
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,350
she would've gone with Qiao Beiyu.

142
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:19,820
Sit tight.

143
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,020
Careful, traffic's heavy.

144
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,110
Qingyu,

145
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:26,390
I think maybe
you've misunderstood your mom.

146
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:31,510
I think your mom really,
really loved your sister.

147
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:35,540
It's just that sometimes,
adults love in ways

148
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:37,990
that are hard to see.

149
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:51,150
Finish your homework after dinner.

150
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,390
Don't wash the dishes.
Just leave them in the sink.

151
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:56,820
I'll clean up when I get back.

152
00:10:57,750 --> 00:11:00,470
Mom, I heard you.

153
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:03,700
Alright.

154
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:12,300
I'm heading back to the shop then.

155
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:18,470
Where are my keys?

156
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:22,270
Right here.

157
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:26,270
Oh.

158
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:34,470
Mom, you don't need
to bring me food anymore.

159
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:35,590
I can cook for myself.

160
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,540
You don't have to
pick me up from school.

161
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:39,230
If you're worried,

162
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:40,540
just call the house.

163
00:11:40,630 --> 00:11:41,780
Check if I'm home on time.

164
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:45,540
I was being immature before.

165
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:47,780
I won't make you worry anymore.

166
00:12:06,725 --> 00:12:11,400
(Qiao's Handmade Noodle House)

167
00:12:26,540 --> 00:12:28,870
I think Qing has a point too.

168
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:31,230
The shop is busy every day,

169
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:32,700
and you still fetch her.

170
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:34,110
That's exhausting.

171
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:36,660
Yeah, Aunt Fanghao.

172
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:40,020
It's been a long time
since what happened with Jinrui.

173
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:41,700
Qing has already learned her lesson.

174
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:43,020
Didn't you say

175
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:44,660
she did better on her midterms too?

176
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:56,820
Hello, Qiao's Noodle Shop.

177
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,150
It's a call from home.

178
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:06,390
Your grandpa fell last night on his way

179
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:07,270
to the bathroom.

180
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:08,510
He couldn't even stand back up.

181
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:10,700
And they're short on help right now.

182
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:13,150
So they want your mom
to go back and help out.

183
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:15,880
But Mom's still sick.

184
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,300
You can't expect someone who's sick

185
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:18,800
to take care of another patient.

186
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:19,420
Who's sick?

187
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:20,990
I'm not sick.

188
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:22,820
I left the money in the small bag.

189
00:13:23,990 --> 00:13:25,820
Didn't we agree on this?

190
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:28,080
The old house belongs
to Uncle Haisheng's family,

191
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:30,150
so he'll be the one
looking after Grandpa and Grandma.

192
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:32,750
Our side and Uncle Jiangsheng's
just pitch in with money.

193
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:35,180
Why are we giving money
and doing the work now?

194
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:37,470
You kids don't understand some things.

195
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:39,700
You can't be
so calculating with families.

196
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,590
If you want fairness,

197
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:44,780
you caused such a scene back then.

198
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,110
Jinrui even lost his job because of you.

199
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:48,870
To be honest, we still owe them.

200
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:50,940
I just feel like

201
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:52,780
not going back would be kind of wrong.

202
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:54,540
And your grandparents say

203
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:56,320
they really do feel bad toward us.

204
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,270
We're family, after all.

205
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:58,630
We are always connected.

206
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:01,270
Our roots are in Nanqiao.

207
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:04,230
When your dad and I get old,
we'll have to go back too.

208
00:14:09,540 --> 00:14:12,350
And your sister is still there.

209
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,700
Looks like you're finally free.

210
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:55,270
No one is around

211
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:57,060
to keep watching you
like a prisoner anymore.

212
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:10,870
Don't you think

213
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:14,150
Nanqiao Village is
like a long piece of string?

214
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:16,660
No matter how far we go,

215
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:18,150
one gentle tug

216
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:20,900
and it pulls us right back
to where we started.

217
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:24,540
The harder we try to run,

218
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,510
the more ridiculous it feels.

219
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:31,700
I think

220
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:34,660
I kind of get it now.

221
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:11,300
(Qiao's Handmade Noodle House)

222
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:15,560
Add a bit of vinegar.

223
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:16,350
I'm adding it first.

224
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:16,990
Okay.

225
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,270
Come on, you should try it.

226
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:19,720
Gives it a little different flavor.

227
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:20,420
Yeah, exactly.

228
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:22,870
You should add some too.

229
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:23,510
I will.

230
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:25,390
Qingyu, your mom's been back home

231
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,750
for over two months now, right?

232
00:16:26,870 --> 00:16:27,870
Why isn't she back yet?

233
00:16:28,230 --> 00:16:29,990
My grandpa's condition keeps flaring up.

234
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:30,900
He needs someone there.

235
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:32,990
That's the thing with old folks.

236
00:16:32,990 --> 00:16:34,270
Falling is the worst for them.

237
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:36,700
Did you guys hear?

238
00:16:36,990 --> 00:16:38,990
Wang passed away last night.

239
00:16:41,990 --> 00:16:42,900
Which Wang?

240
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,110
The one from our neighborhood.

241
00:16:45,350 --> 00:16:47,750
Your good friend, Wang Mumu's dad.

242
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:51,540
So, we've got to live well while we can.

243
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:53,270
Health is the most important thing.

244
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:56,660
Clean sheets and covers

245
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,820
are in the cabinet in my room.

246
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,900
Remember to unplug
the mosquito repellent in the morning.

247
00:17:00,940 --> 00:17:02,180
It's dangerous if you don't.

248
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:03,660
Also,

249
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:05,660
don't set the AC too low.

250
00:17:05,870 --> 00:17:07,550
Keep it around 25 or 26 degrees.

251
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:09,180
Too low wastes electricity.

252
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:10,590
Got it, Mom.

253
00:17:10,740 --> 00:17:11,590
I'm hanging up now.

254
00:17:14,660 --> 00:17:15,550
Is the bed ready?

255
00:17:20,260 --> 00:17:21,070
Sis.

256
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:23,460
I've noticed you've been
in a better mood lately.

257
00:17:23,790 --> 00:17:26,700
You're super patient
with Mom, and really thoughtful too.

258
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:28,870
Are you actually the real Qiao Qingyu?

259
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:31,550
You tell me. Do I look fake?

260
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,830
It still tastes the same.

261
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:52,150
When Dad used to pick me up from school,

262
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:54,030
he always bought me a bottle.

263
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:55,940
Mom never let me drink it.

264
00:17:57,310 --> 00:17:58,900
I finished it in secret
before going home.

265
00:18:00,630 --> 00:18:03,110
It was a little secret
between me and Dad.

266
00:18:04,030 --> 00:18:04,980
Mom never knew.

267
00:18:09,390 --> 00:18:10,180
These past few days,

268
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,460
I've been so busy

269
00:18:12,660 --> 00:18:15,870
running between the hospital,
funeral home,

270
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:16,700
and cemetery.

271
00:18:17,220 --> 00:18:19,500
That's when I realized how many things

272
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,260
you have to take care of when one dies.

273
00:18:22,980 --> 00:18:25,900
I went to the police station
and canceled my dad's registration.

274
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:27,980
Now on our household record,

275
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:31,420
it's just me and my mom.

276
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:39,070
Last night, while packing my bags,

277
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:41,350
I found something.

278
00:18:42,590 --> 00:18:44,900
Turns out my dad kept
all the birthday cards

279
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:47,460
I made for him when I was little.

280
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:50,070
There were seven in total.

281
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:53,390
From when I was three
all the way to nine.

282
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,350
After that,

283
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:57,390
his business failed.

284
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:01,390
And our whole life took a turn
for the worse.

285
00:19:05,390 --> 00:19:07,590
Looking at those cards made me think...

286
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:11,660
If only we could turn back time,

287
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:15,220
back to when we were little,
wouldn't that be nice?

288
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:23,350
Oh right.

289
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:24,900
I forgot to tell you.

290
00:19:24,980 --> 00:19:26,870
I got accepted to Yanbei University.

291
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:29,390
Congrats.

292
00:19:40,460 --> 00:19:44,110
I'm planning to take Mom to Beining.

293
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,420
There's still a bit left
from the loan we took

294
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:49,500
to pay for Dad's treatment.

295
00:19:49,660 --> 00:19:51,980
My aunts say
we don't need to pay it back.

296
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:55,070
They want me to use it

297
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:56,440
to settle down in Beining with Mom.

298
00:19:57,550 --> 00:19:58,980
Will you ever come back?

299
00:20:00,630 --> 00:20:01,660
I don't know.

300
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:05,700
I don't have a home in Huanzhou anymore.

301
00:20:13,110 --> 00:20:14,550
What if I miss you?

302
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:21,350
Just call me.

303
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,870
Or write me a letter.

304
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:24,310
After you graduate,

305
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:25,700
you can come visit me in Beining.

306
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:31,790
I won't forget you.

307
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,310
You can't forget me either.

308
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:35,740
I promise.

309
00:20:47,030 --> 00:20:47,830
Qingyu.

310
00:20:49,180 --> 00:20:51,590
To be honest,
I've always admired Ming Sheng.

311
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:54,940
When I told you not to accept him,

312
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:56,630
I was being selfish.

313
00:21:02,150 --> 00:21:02,980
I know.

314
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:06,740
You knew?

315
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,460
I'm heading off now.

316
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,310
Thanks, everyone.

317
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:36,980
Bye.

318
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:39,660
Xiaohong.

319
00:21:39,870 --> 00:21:40,660
I'm leaving now.

320
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:41,350
Okay, bye.

321
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,070
Bye.

322
00:21:43,660 --> 00:21:44,590
Oh, right.

323
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:46,870
Wang.

324
00:21:47,310 --> 00:21:50,110
That patient in bed six
still has no one to stay with them.

325
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:51,460
Go ask the caregiver station

326
00:21:51,460 --> 00:21:52,550
when someone can come over.

327
00:21:52,550 --> 00:21:53,110
Got it.

328
00:21:53,110 --> 00:21:54,180
Sorry to trouble you.

329
00:21:54,310 --> 00:21:55,110
Yanqiu.

330
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:58,070
Waiting for your dad?

331
00:21:58,220 --> 00:21:58,740
Yeah.

332
00:21:59,630 --> 00:22:01,790
Doesn't your language program
include housing?

333
00:22:01,790 --> 00:22:03,500
Why do you keep coming here?

334
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:05,940
Well, it's just my dad at home.

335
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:07,030
He's all by himself.

336
00:22:07,390 --> 00:22:10,110
I'm just looking out
for a senior living alone.

337
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:11,900
Did Yanqiu already leave?

338
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:12,870
I think she just left.

339
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:16,590
Head Nurse.

340
00:22:16,590 --> 00:22:18,500
Trying to set Yanqiu up again?

341
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,260
That's right.

342
00:22:19,350 --> 00:22:22,310
I even told her to wait for me.

343
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:23,420
Ms. Zhang.

344
00:22:24,070 --> 00:22:24,830
Ming Sheng.

345
00:22:25,030 --> 00:22:26,310
Did you see Yanqiu anywhere?

346
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,310
No, I didn't.

347
00:22:28,460 --> 00:22:30,110
The second she hears about matchmaking,

348
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:31,550
she runs faster than a rabbit.

349
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:32,870
Ms. Zhang,

350
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:35,420
are all these guys for Yanqiu?

351
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:36,070
Of course.

352
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,220
Look at this one.

353
00:22:38,220 --> 00:22:40,390
Graduated from a top university.
He's a civil servant.

354
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:41,830
Handsome and capable.

355
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:42,980
A civil servant?

356
00:22:42,980 --> 00:22:43,550
Exactly.

357
00:22:45,220 --> 00:22:46,500
And this one?

358
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:47,830
Not as educated,

359
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:49,390
but his family got resettlement money.

360
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:50,870
They were given multiple houses.

361
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:51,940
And he's good-looking too.

362
00:22:52,790 --> 00:22:53,940
So, he's probably loaded.

363
00:22:55,180 --> 00:22:56,390
There's this one too.

364
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:58,790
His parents are
both university professors.

365
00:22:58,880 --> 00:22:59,460
In the future,

366
00:22:59,460 --> 00:23:01,390
they will definitely
get along great as a family.

367
00:23:01,390 --> 00:23:02,070
Right?

368
00:23:02,070 --> 00:23:02,940
Indeed.

369
00:23:04,070 --> 00:23:04,660
Here's another.

370
00:23:04,660 --> 00:23:05,390
More?

371
00:23:07,110 --> 00:23:09,310
Why am I telling all this to a kid?

372
00:23:09,550 --> 00:23:10,870
I'm off to find Yanqiu.

373
00:23:10,870 --> 00:23:11,590
Alright.

374
00:23:11,590 --> 00:23:12,500
Bye, Ms. Zhang.

375
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:13,310
Bye-bye.

376
00:23:16,310 --> 00:23:17,110
Is she gone?

377
00:23:21,420 --> 00:23:22,390
That was close.

378
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:23,980
Our head nurse is terrifying.

379
00:23:24,030 --> 00:23:25,700
Come on, let's go.

380
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:29,310
Ms. Yanqiu.

381
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:31,150
Are you not going to consider it?

382
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:33,030
Those guys were actually pretty decent.

383
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:34,600
I'd be tempted myself.

384
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:35,940
Say that again and I'll hit you.

385
00:23:38,070 --> 00:23:39,460
But seriously though,

386
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,180
you keep turning down blind dates.

387
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:43,500
Is it because you already like someone?

388
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:45,870
Really?

389
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:48,590
Then, go for it.

390
00:23:48,870 --> 00:23:50,550
Try to get out of singlehood soon.

391
00:23:52,390 --> 00:23:53,390
When it comes to love,

392
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:55,550
it's not up to just one person.

393
00:23:56,390 --> 00:23:57,660
You'll get it when you're older.

394
00:24:04,980 --> 00:24:05,390
Dad.

395
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:05,940
Hmm?

396
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:07,940
What brings you here?

397
00:24:08,390 --> 00:24:09,350
Did you eat?

398
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:10,420
Yeah.

399
00:24:16,940 --> 00:24:18,350
I just saw Ms. Zhang outside.

400
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:22,180
She was introducing some guys to Yanqiu.

401
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:25,420
Honestly,

402
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:28,070
those guys seemed pretty impressive.

403
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:30,870
I bet Yanqiu was kind of into it.

404
00:24:34,830 --> 00:24:36,900
Didn't know you were into gossip.

405
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:38,500
How am I gossiping?

406
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:39,700
I'm just worried, alright?

407
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:42,420
Yanqiu is so gentle and kind.

408
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:43,590
She wouldn't hurt a fly.

409
00:24:43,870 --> 00:24:45,030
What if some guy out there

410
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:46,070
tricks her or something?

411
00:24:48,830 --> 00:24:50,830
Are we even talking about
the same Fang Yanqiu?

412
00:24:51,420 --> 00:24:52,830
Don't change the subject.

413
00:24:53,630 --> 00:24:54,310
Answer me this.

414
00:24:54,870 --> 00:24:57,110
If Yanqiu really fell for someone else,

415
00:24:57,310 --> 00:24:58,310
what would you do?

416
00:24:59,870 --> 00:25:04,030
If she truly found someone she liked,

417
00:25:06,420 --> 00:25:07,500
I'd wish her well.

418
00:25:12,460 --> 00:25:15,612
(Invitation, 2009)

419
00:25:19,590 --> 00:25:23,420
Huanzhou Outstanding
Healthcare Worker Awards Ceremony.

420
00:25:28,980 --> 00:25:31,660
Dad, I'll go with you.

421
00:25:37,500 --> 00:25:37,980
Here.

422
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:39,870
Freshly made.

423
00:25:40,220 --> 00:25:41,790
Add however many scoops you like.

424
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:42,500
Okay.

425
00:25:49,180 --> 00:25:50,260
Wow, that's a lot.

426
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:52,980
Hey now.

427
00:25:54,310 --> 00:25:56,900
We Shunyun folks can handle our spice,

428
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:58,030
but you and Bei

429
00:25:58,030 --> 00:25:59,500
are the only ones I know

430
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:00,940
who dip sugar into chili oil.

431
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:02,700
And every single time...

432
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:10,070
Go on, eat.

433
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:11,150
Dad.

434
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:16,220
Do you regret sending Qiao Beiyu
back to Nanqiao Village?

435
00:26:23,940 --> 00:26:25,310
We really let her down.

436
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,870
Finish it and get back to your homework.

437
00:26:29,870 --> 00:26:31,420
Or your mom's going to call again.

438
00:26:36,312 --> 00:26:39,962
(2008 Huanzhou Outstanding
Healthcare Worker Awards Ceremony)

439
00:26:44,790 --> 00:26:45,390
Dr. Ming.

440
00:26:45,390 --> 00:26:45,680
Eh?

441
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:46,660
You haven't gone in yet?

442
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:48,000
Oh, I'm waiting for my son.

443
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,630
Alright, you wait here then. I'll go in.

444
00:26:49,630 --> 00:26:50,420
Okay.

445
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:06,590
Where's Ming Sheng?

446
00:27:08,630 --> 00:27:11,030
Ming Sheng told me to come.
He said it was an emergency.

447
00:27:22,110 --> 00:27:23,310
What are you up to?

448
00:27:23,830 --> 00:27:24,590
Setting people up.

449
00:27:24,590 --> 00:27:25,350
You're what?

450
00:27:26,260 --> 00:27:28,310
What exactly is going on here?

451
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:29,220
Come on.

452
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,870
You don't really think
your secret thing with Ms. Yanqiu

453
00:27:31,870 --> 00:27:33,030
was flawless, do you?

454
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:34,390
Like no one ever noticed?

455
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:37,150
We already broke up.

456
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:39,700
I know.

457
00:27:40,420 --> 00:27:42,460
But I can tell you both still care.

458
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:45,900
Dad, you've already sacrificed so much

459
00:27:46,030 --> 00:27:47,700
for your career and me.

460
00:27:47,830 --> 00:27:50,110
It's time you were honest with yourself
and went after

461
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:51,420
what really makes you happy.

462
00:27:52,310 --> 00:27:53,500
Most importantly,

463
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:55,350
neither I nor Ms. Yanqiu

464
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:57,630
need you to
sacrifice yourself on our behalf.

465
00:27:57,870 --> 00:27:59,070
Only when you're happy

466
00:27:59,070 --> 00:28:01,980
can the people around you
truly be happy too. Got it?

467
00:28:02,260 --> 00:28:03,660
Alright.

468
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:06,120
Pass her the phone.

469
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:07,420
I want to talk to Ms. Yanqiu.

470
00:28:07,420 --> 00:28:08,070
Huh?

471
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:09,070
Hurry up.

472
00:28:09,390 --> 00:28:10,900
Okay.

473
00:28:18,180 --> 00:28:18,830
Hello?

474
00:28:19,220 --> 00:28:20,220
Hi, Ms. Yanqiu.

475
00:28:21,390 --> 00:28:23,460
I'm leaving
my uptight dad in your hands.

476
00:28:23,700 --> 00:28:24,500
Also,

477
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:26,420
I'm not calling you miss anymore.

478
00:28:26,420 --> 00:28:27,630
I'll call you "Auntie" instead.

479
00:28:27,830 --> 00:28:29,220
Just to keep things proper.

480
00:28:30,180 --> 00:28:30,940
I'm hanging up now.

481
00:28:41,630 --> 00:28:42,630
Since you're here,

482
00:28:42,700 --> 00:28:44,940
why don't you come in with me?

483
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:47,500
I'd better not.

484
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:49,350
It's full of colleagues in there.

485
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:51,150
We run into each other all the time.

486
00:28:51,740 --> 00:28:53,390
If we walk in together,

487
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,940
people might get the wrong idea.

488
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:04,725
(2008 Huanzhou Outstanding
Healthcare Worker Awards Ceremony)

489
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:13,660
Dr. Ming, this way please.

490
00:29:25,590 --> 00:29:27,790
Ms. Le Fan, you wanted to see me?

491
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:30,590
While sorting files at the association,

492
00:29:30,870 --> 00:29:32,900
I found a digital camcorder
Qiao Beiyu left behind.

493
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:35,420
Technically, it's her private stuff,

494
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:36,900
and I should've kept it to myself.

495
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:39,150
But after thinking it through,

496
00:29:40,220 --> 00:29:41,630
I decided to give it to you.

497
00:30:22,310 --> 00:30:23,700
My name is Qiao Beiyu.

498
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:26,030
I'm twenty-two years old.

499
00:30:27,310 --> 00:30:30,150
I am living with HIV.

500
00:30:34,870 --> 00:30:36,070
I heard that

501
00:30:37,870 --> 00:30:39,460
when I was born,

502
00:30:40,260 --> 00:30:42,980
my grandparents had been
waiting outside the delivery room.

503
00:30:43,350 --> 00:30:45,460
But the moment
they found out I was a girl,

504
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:47,940
they didn't even take a look at me.

505
00:30:48,260 --> 00:30:50,030
They just went back to Nanqiao Village.

506
00:30:51,790 --> 00:30:53,030
Now that I think about it,

507
00:30:56,870 --> 00:31:00,500
maybe that was the moment
it was all decided

508
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:04,420
that I would
only bring them disappointment.

509
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:10,220
(Qiao's Handmade Noodle House)

510
00:31:10,220 --> 00:31:11,550
Let's tie up your hair, okay?

511
00:31:11,550 --> 00:31:12,070
Okay.

512
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:13,180
Hold still.

513
00:31:13,180 --> 00:31:14,310
There, all tied up.

514
00:31:15,420 --> 00:31:17,030
You look so pretty.

515
00:31:17,030 --> 00:31:18,310
Your hair is all done.

516
00:31:20,900 --> 00:31:22,260
Before I turned six,

517
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:25,900
I lived with my parents.

518
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:28,940
We stayed together in the Shunyun.

519
00:31:30,110 --> 00:31:31,460
We didn't have much money,

520
00:31:31,940 --> 00:31:34,180
but as the only child in the family,

521
00:31:34,870 --> 00:31:38,220
(Qiao's Handmade Noodle House)
I had all of their love and attention.

522
00:31:39,900 --> 00:31:42,030
That was the time in my life

523
00:31:43,630 --> 00:31:45,830
when I felt the most carefree.

524
00:31:57,220 --> 00:32:01,550
Then, Qing was born.

525
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:05,310
She was a girl too.

526
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:10,110
Grandma and Grandpa thought
my parents would be too busy,

527
00:32:10,220 --> 00:32:12,940
so they just brought me
back to Nanqiao Village.

528
00:32:15,390 --> 00:32:16,350
Mommy!

529
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:17,630
Mommy!

530
00:32:20,590 --> 00:32:21,550
Go with Grandma.

531
00:32:22,220 --> 00:32:23,220
It's okay.

532
00:32:26,350 --> 00:32:27,260
Don't worry, alright?

533
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:28,110
Go with Grandma.

534
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:29,150
Go with Grandma.

535
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:30,870
Come on, let's go.

536
00:32:30,870 --> 00:32:33,790
Mommy, I don't want to go.

537
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:34,630
It's alright.

538
00:32:34,630 --> 00:32:35,500
It's alright, sweetie.

539
00:32:35,500 --> 00:32:38,740
Mommy, I don't want to go!

540
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:39,940
Come on, let's go.

541
00:32:39,940 --> 00:32:41,830
Mommy!

542
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:43,030
The grown-ups said

543
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:46,550
once my little brother was born,

544
00:32:47,870 --> 00:32:50,070
I'd be able to go back to my parents.

545
00:32:50,830 --> 00:32:51,830
I threw it away!

546
00:32:53,830 --> 00:32:54,790
Where did it go?

547
00:32:54,870 --> 00:32:57,220
So I waited and waited.

548
00:32:58,260 --> 00:33:00,420
And then, my little brother Yu
was finally born.

549
00:33:03,390 --> 00:33:04,390
Where did it go?

550
00:33:04,900 --> 00:33:07,390
But my parents
never kept their promise.

551
00:33:14,030 --> 00:33:15,500
I was the extra one.

552
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:20,500
Nobody needed me.

553
00:33:26,180 --> 00:33:27,500
Except for Jinrui.

554
00:33:29,030 --> 00:33:29,630
You light it.

555
00:33:29,630 --> 00:33:30,660
No, I don't want to.

556
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:31,980
You do it yourself.

557
00:33:31,980 --> 00:33:33,500
Alright, I'll do it then.

558
00:33:38,500 --> 00:33:39,310
Wow.

559
00:33:39,420 --> 00:33:40,900
